oton source, or could be considered part of the reagent system\n\nActually, in PCC chemistry, the pyridinium is part of the reagent (PCC = pyridinium chlorochromate). But since they're listed separately here, and the question asks for roles:\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. In the reaction as written:\n- The alcohol is the substrate\n- CH2Cl2 is the solvent\n- The chlorochromate (CrO3Cl-) is the oxidant/reagent\n- The pyridinium (C5H5NH+) is the catalyst (it's the counterion that makes PCC soluble and acts as a mild acid catalyst)\n\nThe expected output schema is \"condition_role_mapping\". Let me provide a structured answer.\n\nRoles:\n- CC1=C[C@H](O)[C@]2(Cl)[C@H](C1)C(F)(F)[C@@]2(F)Cl: substrate\n- ClCCl: solvent\n- O=[Cr](=O)([O-])Cl: reagent (oxidant)\n- c1cc[nH+]cc1: catalyst"
